#- 


§0           Part 2§r


§0           Liquor§r
#- Part 2 is based on the first edition of CivRealms Liquor. In this part, only the simple and efficient are present. There is a lot to making "booze" but we won't get into that here. Most ingridients are available around the world, so it adds some variation
#- to said liquor. Timing is more forgiving than beer. There are a few ingredients that you may try to find new recipies: melon, netherberry and pumpkin, for example.
§0Anyway, here are the recipies.§r
#- Smooth vodka 
§0There are 3 variations, only the ingredients differ.§r
§0Ingredients§r
§04 hay bales OR§r
§018 beets OR§r
§018 potatoes§r
§0Cooking time§r
§06 minutes§r
§0Not barrel aged§r
§0Distilled 3 times§r
#- Apple Cider
§0Ingredients§r
§013 apples§r
§0Cooking time§r
§07 minutes§r
§03.5-4 years of aging in a birch barrel§r
§0Not distilled§r
#- Tropical cachaca
§0Ingredients§r
§025 sugarcane§r
§0Cooking time§r
§012 minutes§r
§01 year of aging in a jungle barrel§r
§0Not distilled§r
#- Golden rum
§0Ingredients§r
§018 sugar§r
§0Cooking time§r
§017.5 minutes§r
§0??? years of aging in jungle barrel§r
§0Not distilled§r
§0Brew PAST the 17 minute mark§r
#- Tequila
§0Ingredients§r
§010 cacti§r
§0Cooking time §r
§020 minutes§r
§0Aging in jungle barrel is optional.§r
§0Distilled 2 times§r
#- As this is the first edition of the collective CivRealms brewing recipie book, many recipies are unknown,  new recipies will be added in the future.
§0Good luck brewing!§r
